<section id=3D"common-concepts">
<h2>Common Concepts<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.espressif.c=
om/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/contribute/esp-idf-tests-with-pytest.ht=
ml#common-concepts" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81</a></h2>
<p>A <strong>test app</strong> is a set of binaries which are built from an=
 IDF project that is used to test a particular feature of your project. Tes=
t apps are usually located under <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslat=
e"><span class=3D"pre">${IDF_PATH}/examples</span></code>, <code class=3D"d=
ocutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">${IDF_PATH}/tools/test_app=
s</span></code>, and <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span cla=
ss=3D"pre">${IDF_PATH}/components/&lt;COMPONENT_NAME&gt;/test_apps</span></=
code>.</p>
<p>A <strong>Device under test (DUT)</strong> is a set of ESP chip(s) which=
 connect to a host (e.g., a PC). The host is responsible for flashing the a=
pps to the DUT, triggering the test cases, and inspecting the test results.=
</p>
<p>A typical ESP-IDF project that contains a pytest script will have the fo=
llowing structure:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-text notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre id=
=3D"codecell2"><span></span>.
=E2=94=94=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 my_app/
    =E2=94=9C=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 main/
    =E2=94=82   =E2=94=94=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 ...
    =E2=94=9C=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 CMakeLists.txt
    =E2=94=94=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 pytest_foo.py
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell2">
      <svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class=3D"icon icon-tabler i=
con-tabler-copy" width=3D"44" height=3D"44" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" stroke-wi=
dth=3D"1.5" stroke=3D"#000000" fill=3D"none" stroke-linecap=3D"round" strok=
e-linejoin=3D"round">
  <title>Copy to clipboard</title>
  <path stroke=3D"none" d=3D"M0 0h24v24H0z" fill=3D"none"></path>
  <rect x=3D"8" y=3D"8" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" rx=3D"2"></rect>
  <path d=3D"M16 8v-2a2 2 0 0 0 -2 -2h-8a2 2 0 0 0 -2 2v8a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h2">=
</path>
</svg>
    </button></div>
</div>
<p>Sometimes, for some multi-dut tests, one test case requires multiple tes=
t apps. In this case, the test app folder structure would be like this:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-text notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre id=
=3D"codecell3"><span></span>.
=E2=94=9C=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 my_app_foo/
=E2=94=82   =E2=94=9C=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 main/
=E2=94=82   =E2=94=82   =E2=94=94=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 ...
=E2=94=82   =E2=94=94=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 CMakeLists.txt
=E2=94=9C=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 my_app_bar/
=E2=94=82   =E2=94=9C=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 main/
=E2=94=82   =E2=94=82   =E2=94=94=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 ...
=E2=94=82   =E2=94=94=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 CMakeLists.txt
=E2=94=94=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 pytest_foo_bar.py
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell3">
      <svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class=3D"icon icon-tabler i=
con-tabler-copy" width=3D"44" height=3D"44" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" stroke-wi=
dth=3D"1.5" stroke=3D"#000000" fill=3D"none" stroke-linecap=3D"round" strok=
e-linejoin=3D"round">
  <title>Copy to clipboard</title>
  <path stroke=3D"none" d=3D"M0 0h24v24H0z" fill=3D"none"></path>
  <rect x=3D"8" y=3D"8" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" rx=3D"2"></rect>
  <path d=3D"M16 8v-2a2 2 0 0 0 -2 -2h-8a2 2 0 0 0 -2 2v8a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h2">=
</path>
</svg>
    </button></div>
</div>
</section>
<section id=3D"pytest-in-esp-idf">
<h2>pytest in ESP-IDF<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.espressif=
.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/contribute/esp-idf-tests-with-pytest.=
html#pytest-in-esp-idf" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81</a></=
h2>
<section id=3D"single-dut-test-cases">
<h3>Single DUT Test Cases<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.espre=
ssif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/contribute/esp-idf-tests-with-pyt=
est.html#single-dut-test-cases" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=
=81</a></h3>
<section id=3D"getting-started">
<h4>Getting Started<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.espressif.c=
om/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/contribute/esp-idf-tests-with-pytest.ht=
ml#getting-started" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81</a></h4>
<div class=3D"highlight-python notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre i=
d=3D"codecell4"><span></span><span class=3D"nd">@pytest</span><span class=
=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">mark</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span=
 class=3D"n">parametrize</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s1"=
>'target'</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"p">[</span>
    <span class=3D"s1">'esp32'</span><span class=3D"p">,</span>
    <span class=3D"s1">'esp32s2'</span><span class=3D"p">,</span>
<span class=3D"p">],</span> <span class=3D"n">indirect</span><span class=3D=
"o">=3D</span><span class=3D"kc">True</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"nd">@pytest</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n=
">mark</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">generic</span>
<span class=3D"k">def</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"nf">te=
st_hello_world</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"n">dut</span>=
<span class=3D"p">)</span> <span class=3D"o">-&gt;</span> <span class=3D"kc=
">None</span><span class=3D"p">:</span>
    <span class=3D"n">dut</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n"=
>expect</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s1">'Hello world!'</=
span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell4">
      <svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class=3D"icon icon-tabler i=
con-tabler-copy" width=3D"44" height=3D"44" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" stroke-wi=
dth=3D"1.5" stroke=3D"#000000" fill=3D"none" stroke-linecap=3D"round" strok=
e-linejoin=3D"round">
  <title>Copy to clipboard</title>
  <path stroke=3D"none" d=3D"M0 0h24v24H0z" fill=3D"none"></path>
  <rect x=3D"8" y=3D"8" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" rx=3D"2"></rect>
  <path d=3D"M16 8v-2a2 2 0 0 0 -2 -2h-8a2 2 0 0 0 -2 2v8a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h2">=
</path>
</svg>
    </button></div>
</div>
<p>This is a simple test script that could run with the ESP-IDF getting-sta=
rted example <a class=3D"reference external" href=3D"https://github.com/esp=
ressif/esp-idf/tree/v6.0.2/examples/get-started/hello_world">get-started/he=
llo_world</a>.</p>
<p>In this test script, the <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><s=
pan class=3D"pre">@pytest.mark.parametrize</span></code> decorator is used =
to parameterize the test case. The <code class=3D"docutils literal notransl=
ate"><span class=3D"pre">target</span></code> parameter is a special parame=
ter that indicates the target board type. The <code class=3D"docutils liter=
al notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">indirect=3DTrue</span></code> argument =
indicates that this parameter is pre-calculated before other fixtures.</p>
<p>Next is the environment marker. The <code class=3D"docutils literal notr=
anslate"><span class=3D"pre">@pytest.mark.generic</span></code> marker indi=
cates that this test case should run on the generic board type.</p>
<div class=3D"admonition note">
<p class=3D"admonition-title">Note</p>
<p>For the detailed explanation of the environment markers, please refer to=
 <a class=3D"reference external" href=3D"https://github.com/espressif/esp-i=
df/blob/v6.0.2/pytest.ini">env_markers definition </a></p>
</div>
<p>Finally, we have the test function. With a <code class=3D"docutils liter=
al notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">dut</span></code> fixture. In single-du=
t test cases, the <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">dut</span></code> fixture is an instance of <code class=3D"docutil=
s literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">IdfDut</span></code> class, for =
multi-dut test cases, it is a tuple of <code class=3D"docutils literal notr=
anslate"><span class=3D"pre">IdfDut</span></code> instances. For more detai=
ls regarding the <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">IdfDut</span></code> class, please refer to <a class=3D"reference =
external" href=3D"https://docs.espressif.com/projects/pytest-embedded/en/la=
test/api.html#pytest_embedded_idf.dut.IdfDut">pytest-embedded IdfDut API re=
ference</a>.</p>
</section>
<section id=3D"same-app-with-different-sdkconfig-files">
<h4>Same App With Different sdkconfig Files<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"=
https://docs.espressif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/contribute/esp-=
idf-tests-with-pytest.html#same-app-with-different-sdkconfig-files" title=
=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81</a></h4>
<p>For some test cases, you may need to run the same app with different sdk=
config files. For detailed documentation regarding sdkconfig related concep=
ts, please refer to <a class=3D"reference external" href=3D"https://docs.es=
pressif.com/projects/idf-build-apps/en/latest/explanations/find.html">idf-b=
uild-apps Documentation</a>.</p>
<p>Here's a simple example that demonstrates how to run the same app with d=
ifferent sdkconfig files. Assume we have the following folder structure:</p=
>
<div class=3D"highlight-text notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre id=
=3D"codecell5"><span></span>.
=E2=94=94=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 my_app/
    =E2=94=9C=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 main/
    =E2=94=82   =E2=94=94=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 ...
    =E2=94=9C=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 CMakeLists.txt
    =E2=94=9C=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 sdkconfig.ci.foo
    =E2=94=9C=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 sdkconfig.ci.bar
    =E2=94=94=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 pytest_foo.py
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell5">
      <svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class=3D"icon icon-tabler i=
con-tabler-copy" width=3D"44" height=3D"44" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" stroke-wi=
dth=3D"1.5" stroke=3D"#000000" fill=3D"none" stroke-linecap=3D"round" strok=
e-linejoin=3D"round">
  <title>Copy to clipboard</title>
  <path stroke=3D"none" d=3D"M0 0h24v24H0z" fill=3D"none"></path>
  <rect x=3D"8" y=3D"8" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" rx=3D"2"></rect>
  <path d=3D"M16 8v-2a2 2 0 0 0 -2 -2h-8a2 2 0 0 0 -2 2v8a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h2">=
</path>
</svg>
    </button></div>
</div>
<p>If the test case needs to run all supported targets with these two sdkco=
nfig files, you can use the following code:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre i=
d=3D"codecell6"><span></span><span class=3D"nd">@pytest</span><span class=
=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">mark</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span=
 class=3D"n">parametrize</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s1"=
>'target'</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"p">[</span>
    <span class=3D"s1">'esp32'</span><span class=3D"p">,</span>            =
                <span class=3D"c1"># &lt;-- run with esp32 target</span>
    <span class=3D"s1">'esp32s2'</span><span class=3D"p">,</span>          =
                <span class=3D"c1"># &lt;-- run with esp32s2 target</span>
<span class=3D"p">],</span> <span class=3D"n">indirect</span><span class=3D=
"o">=3D</span><span class=3D"kc">True</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"nd">@pytest</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n=
">mark</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">parametrize</span>=
<span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s1">'config'</span><span class=3D"=
p">,</span> <span class=3D"p">[</span>    <span class=3D"c1"># &lt;-- param=
eterize the sdkconfig file</span>
    <span class=3D"s1">'foo'</span><span class=3D"p">,</span>              =
                <span class=3D"c1"># &lt;-- run with sdkconfig.ci.foo</span=
>
    <span class=3D"s1">'bar'</span><span class=3D"p">,</span>              =
                <span class=3D"c1"># &lt;-- run with sdkconfig.ci.bar</span=
>
<span class=3D"p">],</span> <span class=3D"n">indirect</span><span class=3D=
"o">=3D</span><span class=3D"kc">True</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>     =
                  <span class=3D"c1"># &lt;-- `indirect=3DTrue` is required=
, indicates this param is pre-calculated before other fixtures</span>
<span class=3D"k">def</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"nf">te=
st_foo_bar</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"n">dut</span><spa=
n class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"n">config</span><span class=3D"p">)</=
span> <span class=3D"o">-&gt;</span> <span class=3D"kc">None</span><span cl=
ass=3D"p">:</span>
    <span class=3D"k">if</span> <span class=3D"n">config</span> <span class=
=3D"o">=3D=3D</span> <span class=3D"s1">'foo'</span><span class=3D"p">:</sp=
an>
      <span class=3D"n">dut</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"=
n">expect</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s1">'This is from =
sdkconfig.ci.foo'</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
    <span class=3D"k">elif</span> <span class=3D"n">config</span> <span cla=
ss=3D"o">=3D=3D</span> <span class=3D"s1">'bar'</span><span class=3D"p">:</=
span>
      <span class=3D"n">dut</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"=
n">expect</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s1">'This is from =
sdkconfig.ci.bar'</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell6">
      <svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class=3D"icon icon-tabler i=
con-tabler-copy" width=3D"44" height=3D"44" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" stroke-wi=
dth=3D"1.5" stroke=3D"#000000" fill=3D"none" stroke-linecap=3D"round" strok=
e-linejoin=3D"round">
  <title>Copy to clipboard</title>
  <path stroke=3D"none" d=3D"M0 0h24v24H0z" fill=3D"none"></path>
  <rect x=3D"8" y=3D"8" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" rx=3D"2"></rect>
  <path d=3D"M16 8v-2a2 2 0 0 0 -2 -2h-8a2 2 0 0 0 -2 2v8a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h2">=
</path>
</svg>
    </button></div>
</div>
<p>All markers will impact the test case simultaneously. Overall, this test=
 function would be replicated to 4 test cases:</p>
<ul class=3D"simple">
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">tes=
t_foo_bar</span></code>, with esp32 target, and <code class=3D"docutils lit=
eral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">sdkconfig.ci.foo</span></code> as the=
 sdkconfig file</p></li>
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">tes=
t_foo_bar</span></code>, with esp32 target, and <code class=3D"docutils lit=
eral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">sdkconfig.ci.bar</span></code> as the=
 sdkconfig file</p></li>
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">tes=
t_foo_bar</span></code>, with esp32s2 target, and <code class=3D"docutils l=
iteral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">sdkconfig.ci.foo</span></code> as t=
he sdkconfig file</p></li>
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">tes=
t_foo_bar</span></code>, with esp32s2 target, and <code class=3D"docutils l=
iteral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">sdkconfig.ci.bar</span></code> as t=
he sdkconfig file</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Sometimes in the test script or the log file, you may see the following =
format:</p>
<ul class=3D"simple">
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">esp=
32.foo.test_foo_bar</span></code></p></li>
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">esp=
32.bar.test_foo_bar</span></code></p></li>
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">esp=
32s2.foo.test_foo_bar</span></code></p></li>
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">esp=
32s2.bar.test_foo_bar</span></code></p></li>
</ul>
<p>We call this format the <strong>test case ID</strong>. The test case ID =
should be considered as the unique identifier of a test case. It is compose=
d of the following parts:</p>
<ul class=3D"simple">
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">esp=
32</span></code>: the target name</p></li>
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">foo=
</span></code>: the config name</p></li>
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">tes=
t_foo_bar</span></code>: the test function name</p></li>
</ul>
<p>The test case ID is used to identify the test case in the JUnit report.<=
/p>
<div class=3D"admonition note">
<p class=3D"admonition-title">Note</p>
<p>Nearly all the CLI options of pytest-embedded supports parameterization.=
 To see all supported CLI options, you may run <code class=3D"docutils lite=
ral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">pytest</span> <span class=3D"pre">--he=
lp</span></code> and check the <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"=
><span class=3D"pre">embedded-...</span></code> sections for vanilla pytest=
-embedded ones, and the <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span =
class=3D"pre">idf</span></code> sections for ESP-IDF specific ones.</p>
</div>
</section>
<section id=3D"same-app-with-different-sdkconfig-files-different-targets">
<h4>Same App With Different sdkconfig Files, Different Targets<a class=3D"h=
eaderlink" href=3D"https://docs.espressif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/es=
p32/contribute/esp-idf-tests-with-pytest.html#same-app-with-different-sdkco=
nfig-files-different-targets" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81=
</a></h4>
<p>For some test cases, you may need to run the same app with different sdk=
config files. These sdkconfig files supports different targets. We may use =
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">pytest.par=
am</span></code> to achieve this. Let's use the same folder structure as ab=
ove.</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre i=
d=3D"codecell7"><span></span><span class=3D"nd">@pytest</span><span class=
=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">mark</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span=
 class=3D"n">parametrize</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s1"=
>'config, target'</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"p">[</spa=
n>
    <span class=3D"n">pytest</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D=
"n">param</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s1">'foo'</span><s=
pan class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"s1">'esp32'</span><span class=3D"p"=
>),</span>
    <span class=3D"n">pytest</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D=
"n">param</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s1">'bar'</span><s=
pan class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"s1">'esp32s2'</span><span class=3D"=
p">),</span>
<span class=3D"p">],</span> <span class=3D"n">indirect</span><span class=3D=
"o">=3D</span><span class=3D"kc">True</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell7">
      <svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class=3D"icon icon-tabler i=
con-tabler-copy" width=3D"44" height=3D"44" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" stroke-wi=
dth=3D"1.5" stroke=3D"#000000" fill=3D"none" stroke-linecap=3D"round" strok=
e-linejoin=3D"round">
  <title>Copy to clipboard</title>
  <path stroke=3D"none" d=3D"M0 0h24v24H0z" fill=3D"none"></path>
  <rect x=3D"8" y=3D"8" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" rx=3D"2"></rect>
