</div>
<p>Now this test function would be replicated to 2 test cases (represented =
as test case IDs):</p>
<ul class=3D"simple">
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">esp=
32.foo.test_foo_bar</span></code></p></li>
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">esp=
32s2.bar.test_foo_bar</span></code></p></li>
</ul>
</section>
</section>
<section id=3D"testing-serial-output-expecting">
<h3>Testing Serial Output (Expecting)<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https:=
//docs.espressif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/contribute/esp-idf-te=
sts-with-pytest.html#testing-serial-output-expecting" title=3D"Permalink to=
 this heading">=EF=83=81</a></h3>
<p>To ensure that test has executed successfully on target, the test script=
 can test that serial output of the target using the <code class=3D"docutil=
s literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">dut.expect()</span></code> funct=
ion, for example:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre i=
d=3D"codecell8"><span></span><span class=3D"k">def</span><span class=3D"w">=
 </span><span class=3D"nf">test_hello_world</span><span class=3D"p">(</span=
><span class=3D"n">dut</span><span class=3D"p">)</span> <span class=3D"o">-=
&gt;</span> <span class=3D"kc">None</span><span class=3D"p">:</span>
    <span class=3D"n">dut</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n"=
>expect</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s1">'\d+'</span><spa=
n class=3D"p">)</span>  <span class=3D"c1"># &lt;-- `expect`ing from a rege=
x</span>
    <span class=3D"n">dut</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n"=
>expect_exact</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s1">'Hello wor=
ld!'</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>  <span class=3D"c1"># &lt;-- `expect_=
exact`ly the string</span>
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell8">
      <svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class=3D"icon icon-tabler i=
con-tabler-copy" width=3D"44" height=3D"44" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" stroke-wi=
dth=3D"1.5" stroke=3D"#000000" fill=3D"none" stroke-linecap=3D"round" strok=
e-linejoin=3D"round">
  <title>Copy to clipboard</title>
  <path stroke=3D"none" d=3D"M0 0h24v24H0z" fill=3D"none"></path>
  <rect x=3D"8" y=3D"8" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" rx=3D"2"></rect>
  <path d=3D"M16 8v-2a2 2 0 0 0 -2 -2h-8a2 2 0 0 0 -2 2v8a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h2">=
</path>
</svg>
    </button></div>
</div>
<p>The <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">dut=
.expect(...)</span></code> will first compile the expected string into rege=
x, which in turn is then used to seek through the serial output until the c=
ompiled regex is matched, or until a timeout occurs.</p>
<p>Please pay extra attention to the expected string when it contains regex=
 keyword characters (e.g., parentheses, square brackets). Alternatively, yo=
u may use <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">=
dut.expect_exact(...)</span></code> that will attempt to match the string w=
ithout converting it into regex.</p>
<p>For more information regarding the different types of <code class=3D"doc=
utils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">expect</span></code> functio=
ns, please refer to the <a class=3D"reference external" href=3D"https://doc=
s.espressif.com/projects/pytest-embedded/en/latest/expecting.html">pytest-e=
mbedded Expecting documentation</a>.</p>
</section>
<section id=3D"multi-dut-test-cases">
<h3>Multi-DUT Test Cases<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.espres=
sif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/contribute/esp-idf-tests-with-pyte=
st.html#multi-dut-test-cases" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81=
</a></h3>
<section id=3D"multi-target-tests-with-the-same-app">
<h4>Multi-Target Tests with the Same App<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"htt=
ps://docs.espressif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/contribute/esp-idf=
-tests-with-pytest.html#multi-target-tests-with-the-same-app" title=3D"Perm=
alink to this heading">=EF=83=81</a></h4>
<p>In some cases a test may involve multiple targets running the same test =
app. Parameterize <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">count</span></code> to the number of DUTs you want to test with.</=
p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre i=
d=3D"codecell9"><span></span><span class=3D"nd">@pytest</span><span class=
=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">mark</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span=
 class=3D"n">parametrize</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s1"=
>'count'</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"p">[</span>
    <span class=3D"mi">2</span><span class=3D"p">,</span>
<span class=3D"p">],</span> <span class=3D"n">indirect</span><span class=3D=
"o">=3D</span><span class=3D"kc">True</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"nd">@pytest</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n=
">mark</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">parametrize</span>=
<span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s1">'target'</span><span class=3D"=
p">,</span> <span class=3D"p">[</span>
  <span class=3D"s1">'esp32|esp32s2'</span><span class=3D"p">,</span>
  <span class=3D"s1">'esp32s3'</span><span class=3D"p">,</span>
<span class=3D"p">],</span> <span class=3D"n">indirect</span><span class=3D=
"o">=3D</span><span class=3D"kc">True</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"k">def</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"nf">te=
st_hello_world</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"n">dut</span>=
<span class=3D"p">)</span> <span class=3D"o">-&gt;</span> <span class=3D"kc=
">None</span><span class=3D"p">:</span>
    <span class=3D"n">dut</span><span class=3D"p">[</span><span class=3D"mi=
">0</span><span class=3D"p">]</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=
=3D"n">expect</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s1">'Hello wor=
ld!'</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
    <span class=3D"n">dut</span><span class=3D"p">[</span><span class=3D"mi=
">1</span><span class=3D"p">]</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=
=3D"n">expect</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s1">'Hello wor=
ld!'</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell9">
