<section id=3D"running-target-tests-in-ci">
<h2>Running Target Tests in CI<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.=
espressif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/contribute/esp-idf-tests-wit=
h-pytest.html#running-target-tests-in-ci" title=3D"Permalink to this headin=
g">=EF=83=81</a></h2>
<p>The workflow in CI is as follows:</p>
<figure class=3D"align-center" id=3D"id3">
<div class=3D"align-default"><img height=3D"200" src=3D"https://docs.espres=
sif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/_images/blockdiag-0ecc6d509ba0696a=
16f30998f601f96e6907546f.png" width=3D"832"></div>
<figcaption>
<p><span class=3D"caption-text">Target Test Child Pipeline Workflow</span><=
a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.espressif.com/projects/esp-idf/=
en/stable/esp32/contribute/esp-idf-tests-with-pytest.html#id3" title=3D"Per=
malink to this image">=EF=83=81</a></p>
</figcaption>
</figure>
<p>All build jobs and target test jobs are generated automatically by our C=
I script <a class=3D"reference external" href=3D"https://github.com/espress=
if/esp-idf/tree/v6.0.2/tools/ci/dynamic_pipelines">tools/ci/dynamic_pipelin=
es</a>.</p>
<section id=3D"build-jobs">
<h3>Build Jobs<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.espressif.com/pr=
ojects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/contribute/esp-idf-tests-with-pytest.html#bu=
ild-jobs" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81</a></h3>
<p>In CI, all ESP-IDF projects under <code class=3D"docutils literal notran=
slate"><span class=3D"pre">components</span></code>, <code class=3D"docutil=
s literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">examples</span></code>, and <cod=
e class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">tools/test_app=
s</span></code>, are built with all supported targets and sdkconfig files. =
The binaries are built under <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">build_&lt;target&gt;_&lt;config&gt;</span></code>. For e=
xample</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-text notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre id=
=3D"codecell18"><span></span>.
=E2=94=9C=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 build_esp32_history/
=E2=94=82   =E2=94=94=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 ...
=E2=94=9C=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 build_esp32_nohistory/
=E2=94=82   =E2=94=94=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 ...
=E2=94=9C=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 build_esp32s2_history/
=E2=94=82   =E2=94=94=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 ...
=E2=94=9C=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 ...
=E2=94=9C=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 main/
=E2=94=9C=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 CMakeLists.txt
=E2=94=9C=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 sdkconfig.ci.history
=E2=94=9C=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 sdkconfig.ci.nohistory
=E2=94=94=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 ...
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell18">
      <svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class=3D"icon icon-tabler i=
con-tabler-copy" width=3D"44" height=3D"44" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" stroke-wi=
dth=3D"1.5" stroke=3D"#000000" fill=3D"none" stroke-linecap=3D"round" strok=
e-linejoin=3D"round">
  <title>Copy to clipboard</title>
  <path stroke=3D"none" d=3D"M0 0h24v24H0z" fill=3D"none"></path>
  <rect x=3D"8" y=3D"8" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" rx=3D"2"></rect>
  <path d=3D"M16 8v-2a2 2 0 0 0 -2 -2h-8a2 2 0 0 0 -2 2v8a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h2">=
</path>
</svg>
    </button></div>
</div>
<p>There are two types of build jobs, <code class=3D"docutils literal notra=
nslate"><span class=3D"pre">build_test_related_apps</span></code> and <code=
 class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">build_non_test_=
related_apps</span></code>.</p>
<p>For <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">bui=
ld_test_related_apps</span></code>, all the built binaries will be uploaded=
 to our internal MinIO server. You may find the download link in the build =
report posted in the internal MR.</p>
<p>For <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">bui=
ld_non_test_related_apps</span></code>, all the built binaries will be remo=
ved after the build job is finished. Only the build log files will be uploa=
ded to our internal MinIO server. You may also find the download link in th=
e build report posted in the internal MR.</p>
</section>
<section id=3D"target-test-jobs">
<h3>Target Test Jobs<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.espressif.=
com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/contribute/esp-idf-tests-with-pytest.h=
tml#target-test-jobs" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81</a></h3=
>
<p>In CI, all generated target test jobs are named according to the pattern=
 "&lt;targets&gt; - &lt;env_markers&gt;". For example, single-dut test job =
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">esp32</spa=
n> <span class=3D"pre">-</span> <span class=3D"pre">generic</span></code>, =
or multi-dut test job <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span cl=
ass=3D"pre">esp32,esp32</span> <span class=3D"pre">-</span> <span class=3D"=
pre">multi_dut_generic</span></code>.</p>
<p>The binaries in the target test jobs are downloaded from our internal Mi=
nIO servers. For most of the test cases, only the files that are required b=
y flash (like .bin files, flash_args files, etc) would be downloaded. For s=
ome test cases, like jtag test cases, .elf files are also downloaded.</p>
</section>
</section>
<section id=3D"running-tests-locally">
<span id=3D"run-the-tests-locally"></span><h2>Running Tests Locally<a class=
=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.espressif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stab=
le/esp32/contribute/esp-idf-tests-with-pytest.html#running-tests-locally" t=
itle=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81</a></h2>
<section id=3D"id1">
<h3>Installation<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.espressif.com/=
projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/contribute/esp-idf-tests-with-pytest.html#=
id1" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81</a></h3>
<p>First you need to install ESP-IDF with additional Python requirements:</=
p>
<div class=3D"highlight-shell notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre id=
=3D"codecell19"><span></span>$<span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"nb">=
cd</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"nv">$IDF_PATH</span>
$<span class=3D"w"> </span>bash<span class=3D"w"> </span>install.sh<span cl=
ass=3D"w"> </span>--enable-ci
$<span class=3D"w"> </span>.<span class=3D"w"> </span>./export.sh
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell19">
      <svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class=3D"icon icon-tabler i=
con-tabler-copy" width=3D"44" height=3D"44" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" stroke-wi=
dth=3D"1.5" stroke=3D"#000000" fill=3D"none" stroke-linecap=3D"round" strok=
e-linejoin=3D"round">
  <title>Copy to clipboard</title>
  <path stroke=3D"none" d=3D"M0 0h24v24H0z" fill=3D"none"></path>
  <rect x=3D"8" y=3D"8" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" rx=3D"2"></rect>
  <path d=3D"M16 8v-2a2 2 0 0 0 -2 -2h-8a2 2 0 0 0 -2 2v8a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h2">=
</path>
</svg>
    </button></div>
</div>
</section>
<section id=3D"build-directories">
<h3>Build Directories<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.espressif=
.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/contribute/esp-idf-tests-with-pytest.=
html#build-directories" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81</a></=
h3>
<p>By default, each test case looks for the required binary files in the fo=
llowing directories (in order):</p>
<ul class=3D"simple">
<li><p>Directory set by <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span =
class=3D"pre">--build-dir</span></code> command line argument, if specified=
.</p></li>
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">bui=
ld_&lt;target&gt;_&lt;sdkconfig&gt;</span></code></p></li>
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">bui=
ld_&lt;target&gt;</span></code></p></li>
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">bui=
ld_&lt;sdkconfig&gt;</span></code></p></li>
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">bui=
ld</span></code></p></li>
</ul>
<p>As long as one of the above directories exists, the test case uses that =
directory to flash the binaries. If none of the above directories exists, t=
he test case fails with an error.</p>
</section>
<section id=3D"test-your-test-script">
<h3>Test Your Test Script<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.espre=
ssif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/contribute/esp-idf-tests-with-pyt=
est.html#test-your-test-script" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=
=81</a></h3>
<section id=3D"single-dut-test-cases-with-sdkconfig-defaults">
<h4>Single-DUT Test Cases With <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"=
><span class=3D"pre">sdkconfig.defaults</span></code><a class=3D"headerlink=
" href=3D"https://docs.espressif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/contr=
ibute/esp-idf-tests-with-pytest.html#single-dut-test-cases-with-sdkconfig-d=
efaults" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81</a></h4>
<p>This is the simplest use case. Let's take <a class=3D"reference external=
" href=3D"https://github.com/espressif/esp-idf/tree/v6.0.2/examples/get-sta=
rted/hello_world">examples/get-started/hello_world</a> as an example. Assum=
e we're testing with a ESP32 board.</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-shell notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre id=
=3D"codecell20"><span></span>$<span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"nb">=
cd</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"nv">$IDF_PATH</span>/exam=
ples/get-started/hello_world
$<span class=3D"w"> </span>idf.py<span class=3D"w"> </span>set-target<span =
class=3D"w"> </span>esp32<span class=3D"w"> </span>build
$<span class=3D"w"> </span>pytest<span class=3D"w"> </span>--target<span cl=
ass=3D"w"> </span>esp32
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell20">
      <svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class=3D"icon icon-tabler i=
con-tabler-copy" width=3D"44" height=3D"44" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" stroke-wi=
dth=3D"1.5" stroke=3D"#000000" fill=3D"none" stroke-linecap=3D"round" strok=
e-linejoin=3D"round">
  <title>Copy to clipboard</title>
  <path stroke=3D"none" d=3D"M0 0h24v24H0z" fill=3D"none"></path>
  <rect x=3D"8" y=3D"8" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" rx=3D"2"></rect>
