</div>
</section>
<section id=3D"single-dut-test-cases-with-sdkconfig-ci-xxx">
<h4>Single-DUT Test Cases With <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"=
><span class=3D"pre">sdkconfig.ci.xxx</span></code><a class=3D"headerlink" =
href=3D"https://docs.espressif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/contrib=
ute/esp-idf-tests-with-pytest.html#single-dut-test-cases-with-sdkconfig-ci-=
xxx" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81</a></h4>
<p>Some test cases may need to run with different sdkconfig files. Let's ta=
ke <a class=3D"reference external" href=3D"https://github.com/espressif/esp=
-idf/tree/v6.0.2/examples/system/console/basic">examples/system/console/bas=
ic</a> as an example. Assume we're testing with a ESP32 board, and test wit=
h <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">sdkconfi=
g.ci.history</span></code>.</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-shell notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre id=
=3D"codecell21"><span></span>$<span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"nb">=
cd</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"nv">$IDF_PATH</span>/exam=
ples/system/console/basic
$<span class=3D"w"> </span>idf.py<span class=3D"w"> </span>-DSDKCONFIG_DEFA=
ULTS<span class=3D"o">=3D</span><span class=3D"s1">'sdkconfig.defaults;sdkc=
onfig.ci.history'</span><span class=3D"w"> </span>-B<span class=3D"w"> </sp=
an>build_esp32_history<span class=3D"w"> </span>set-target<span class=3D"w"=
> </span>esp32<span class=3D"w"> </span>build
$<span class=3D"w"> </span>pytest<span class=3D"w"> </span>--target<span cl=
ass=3D"w"> </span>esp32<span class=3D"w"> </span>-k<span class=3D"w"> </spa=
n><span class=3D"s2">"not nohistory"</span>
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell21">
      <svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class=3D"icon icon-tabler i=
con-tabler-copy" width=3D"44" height=3D"44" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" stroke-wi=
dth=3D"1.5" stroke=3D"#000000" fill=3D"none" stroke-linecap=3D"round" strok=
e-linejoin=3D"round">
  <title>Copy to clipboard</title>
  <path stroke=3D"none" d=3D"M0 0h24v24H0z" fill=3D"none"></path>
  <rect x=3D"8" y=3D"8" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" rx=3D"2"></rect>
  <path d=3D"M16 8v-2a2 2 0 0 0 -2 -2h-8a2 2 0 0 0 -2 2v8a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h2">=
</path>
</svg>
    </button></div>
</div>
<div class=3D"admonition note">
<p class=3D"admonition-title">Note</p>
<p>Here if we use <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">pytest</span> <span class=3D"pre">--target</span> <span class=3D"p=
re">esp32</span> <span class=3D"pre">-k</span> <span class=3D"pre">history<=
/span></code>, both test cases will be selected, since <code class=3D"docut=
ils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">pytest</span> <span class=3D"p=
re">-k</span></code> will use string matching to filter the test cases.</p>
</div>
<p>If you want to build and test with all sdkconfig files at the same time,=
 you should use our CI script as an helper script:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-shell notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre id=
=3D"codecell22"><span></span>$<span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"nb">=
cd</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"nv">$IDF_PATH</span>/exam=
ples/system/console/basic
$<span class=3D"w"> </span>idf-ci<span class=3D"w"> </span>build<span class=
=3D"w"> </span>run<span class=3D"w"> </span>--target<span class=3D"w"> </sp=
an>esp32<span class=3D"w"> </span>--only-test-related
$<span class=3D"w"> </span>pytest<span class=3D"w"> </span>--target<span cl=
ass=3D"w"> </span>esp32
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell22">
      <svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class=3D"icon icon-tabler i=
con-tabler-copy" width=3D"44" height=3D"44" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" stroke-wi=
dth=3D"1.5" stroke=3D"#000000" fill=3D"none" stroke-linecap=3D"round" strok=
e-linejoin=3D"round">
  <title>Copy to clipboard</title>
  <path stroke=3D"none" d=3D"M0 0h24v24H0z" fill=3D"none"></path>
  <rect x=3D"8" y=3D"8" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" rx=3D"2"></rect>
  <path d=3D"M16 8v-2a2 2 0 0 0 -2 -2h-8a2 2 0 0 0 -2 2v8a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h2">=
</path>
</svg>
    </button></div>
</div>
<p>The app with <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D=
"pre">sdkconfig.ci.history</span></code> will be built in <code class=3D"do=
cutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">build_esp32_history</span><=
/code>, and the app with <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span=
 class=3D"pre">sdkconfig.ci.nohistory</span></code> will be built in <code =
class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">build_esp32_nohi=
story</span></code>. <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span cla=
ss=3D"pre">pytest</span> <span class=3D"pre">--target</span> <span class=3D=
"pre">esp32</span></code> will run tests on both apps.</p>
</section>
<section id=3D"id2">
<h4>Multi-DUT Test Cases<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.espres=
sif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/contribute/esp-idf-tests-with-pyte=
st.html#id2" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81</a></h4>
<p>Some test cases may need to run with multiple DUTs. Let's take <a class=
=3D"reference external" href=3D"https://github.com/espressif/esp-idf/tree/v=
6.0.2/examples/openthread">examples/openthread</a> as an example. The test =
case function looks like this:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre i=
d=3D"codecell23"><span></span><span class=3D"nd">@pytest</span><span class=
=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">mark</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span=
 class=3D"n">parametrize</span><span class=3D"p">(</span>
    <span class=3D"s1">'config, count, app_path, target'</span><span class=
=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"p">[</span>
        <span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s1">'rcp|cli_h2|br'</span>=
<span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"mi">3</span><span class=3D"p">,</=
span>
         <span class=3D"sa">f</span><span class=3D"s1">'</span><span class=
=3D"si">{</span><span class=3D"n">os</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span =
class=3D"n">path</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">join</sp=
an><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"n">os</span><span class=3D"o">.=
</span><span class=3D"n">path</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=
=3D"n">dirname</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"vm">__file__<=
/span><span class=3D"p">),</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"s=
2">"ot_rcp"</span><span class=3D"p">)</span><span class=3D"si">}</span><spa=
n class=3D"s1">'</span>
         <span class=3D"sa">f</span><span class=3D"s1">'|</span><span class=
=3D"si">{</span><span class=3D"n">os</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span =
class=3D"n">path</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">join</sp=
an><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"n">os</span><span class=3D"o">.=
</span><span class=3D"n">path</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=
=3D"n">dirname</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"vm">__file__<=
/span><span class=3D"p">),</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"s=
2">"ot_cli"</span><span class=3D"p">)</span><span class=3D"si">}</span><spa=
n class=3D"s1">'</span>
         <span class=3D"sa">f</span><span class=3D"s1">'|</span><span class=
=3D"si">{</span><span class=3D"n">os</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span =
class=3D"n">path</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">join</sp=
an><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"n">os</span><span class=3D"o">.=
</span><span class=3D"n">path</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=
=3D"n">dirname</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"vm">__file__<=
/span><span class=3D"p">),</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"s=
2">"ot_br"</span><span class=3D"p">)</span><span class=3D"si">}</span><span=
 class=3D"s1">'</span><span class=3D"p">,</span>
         <span class=3D"s1">'esp32c6|esp32h2|esp32s3'</span><span class=3D"=
p">),</span>
    <span class=3D"p">],</span>
    <span class=3D"n">indirect</span><span class=3D"o">=3D</span><span clas=
s=3D"kc">True</span><span class=3D"p">,</span>
<span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"k">def</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"nf">te=
st_thread_connect</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"n">dut</sp=
an><span class=3D"p">:</span><span class=3D"n">Tuple</span><span class=3D"p=
">[</span><span class=3D"n">IdfDut</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span c=
lass=3D"n">IdfDut</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"n">IdfDut=
</span><span class=3D"p">])</span> <span class=3D"o">-&gt;</span> <span cla=
ss=3D"kc">None</span><span class=3D"p">:</span>
    <span class=3D"o">...</span>
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell23">
      <svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class=3D"icon icon-tabler i=
con-tabler-copy" width=3D"44" height=3D"44" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" stroke-wi=
dth=3D"1.5" stroke=3D"#000000" fill=3D"none" stroke-linecap=3D"round" strok=
e-linejoin=3D"round">
  <title>Copy to clipboard</title>
  <path stroke=3D"none" d=3D"M0 0h24v24H0z" fill=3D"none"></path>
  <rect x=3D"8" y=3D"8" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" rx=3D"2"></rect>
  <path d=3D"M16 8v-2a2 2 0 0 0 -2 -2h-8a2 2 0 0 0 -2 2v8a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h2">=
</path>
</svg>
    </button></div>
</div>
<p>The test cases will run with</p>
<ul class=3D"simple">
<li><p>ESP32-C6, flashed with <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">ot_rcp</span></code></p></li>
<li><p>ESP32-H2, flashed with <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">ot_cli</span></code></p></li>
<li><p>ESP32-S3, flashed with <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">ot_br</span></code></p></li>
</ul>
<p>Of course we can build the required binaries manually, but we can also u=
se our CI script as an helper script:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-shell notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre id=
=3D"codecell24"><span></span>$<span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"nb">=
cd</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"nv">$IDF_PATH</span>/exam=
ples/openthread
$<span class=3D"w"> </span>idf-ci<span class=3D"w"> </span>build<span class=
=3D"w"> </span>run<span class=3D"w"> </span>--only-test-related<span class=
=3D"w"> </span>-k<span class=3D"w"> </span>test_thread_connect
$<span class=3D"w"> </span>pytest<span class=3D"w"> </span>-k<span class=3D=
"w"> </span>test_thread_connect
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell24">
      <svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class=3D"icon icon-tabler i=
con-tabler-copy" width=3D"44" height=3D"44" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" stroke-wi=
dth=3D"1.5" stroke=3D"#000000" fill=3D"none" stroke-linecap=3D"round" strok=
e-linejoin=3D"round">
  <title>Copy to clipboard</title>
  <path stroke=3D"none" d=3D"M0 0h24v24H0z" fill=3D"none"></path>
  <rect x=3D"8" y=3D"8" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" rx=3D"2"></rect>
  <path d=3D"M16 8v-2a2 2 0 0 0 -2 -2h-8a2 2 0 0 0 -2 2v8a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h2">=
</path>
</svg>
    </button></div>
</div>
<div class=3D"admonition important">
<p class=3D"admonition-title">Important</p>
<p>It is mandatory to list all the targets for multi-DUT test cases. Otherw=
ise, the test case would fail with an error.</p>
</div>
</section>
</section>
<section id=3D"debug-ci-test-cases">
<h3>Debug CI Test Cases<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.espress=
if.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/contribute/esp-idf-tests-with-pytes=
t.html#debug-ci-test-cases" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81</=
a></h3>
<p>Sometimes you can't reproduce the CI test case failure locally. In this =
case, you may need to debug the test case with the binaries built in CI.</p=
>
<p>Run pytest with <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">--pipeline-id</span> <span class=3D"pre">&lt;pipeline_id&gt;</span=
></code> to force pytest to download the binaries from CI. For example:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-shell notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre id=
=3D"codecell25"><span></span>$<span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"nb">=
cd</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"nv">$IDF_PATH</span>/exam=
ples/get-started/hello_world
$<span class=3D"w"> </span>pytest<span class=3D"w"> </span>--target<span cl=
ass=3D"w"> </span>esp32<span class=3D"w"> </span>--pipeline-id<span class=
=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"m">123456</span>
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell25">
      <svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class=3D"icon icon-tabler i=
con-tabler-copy" width=3D"44" height=3D"44" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" stroke-wi=
dth=3D"1.5" stroke=3D"#000000" fill=3D"none" stroke-linecap=3D"round" strok=
e-linejoin=3D"round">
  <title>Copy to clipboard</title>
  <path stroke=3D"none" d=3D"M0 0h24v24H0z" fill=3D"none"></path>
  <rect x=3D"8" y=3D"8" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" rx=3D"2"></rect>
  <path d=3D"M16 8v-2a2 2 0 0 0 -2 -2h-8a2 2 0 0 0 -2 2v8a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h2">=
</path>
</svg>
    </button></div>
</div>
<p>Even if you have <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span clas=
s=3D"pre">build_esp32_default</span></code>, or <code class=3D"docutils lit=
eral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">build</span></code> directory locally=
, pytest would still download the binaries from pipeline 123456 and place t=
he binaries in <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"=
pre">build_esp32_default</span></code>. Then run the test case with this bi=
nary.</p>
<div class=3D"admonition note">
<p class=3D"admonition-title">Note</p>
<p>&lt;pipeline_id&gt; should be the parent pipeline id. You can copy it in=
 your MR page.</p>
</div>
</section>
</section>
<section id=3D"pytest-tips-tricks">
<h2>Pytest Tips &amp; Tricks<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.es=
pressif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/contribute/esp-idf-tests-with-=
pytest.html#pytest-tips-tricks" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=
=81</a></h2>
<section id=3D"custom-classes">
<h3>Custom Classes<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.espressif.co=
m/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/contribute/esp-idf-tests-with-pytest.htm=
l#custom-classes" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81</a></h3>
<p>Usually, you may want to write a custom class under these conditions:</p=
>
<ol class=3D"arabic simple">
<li><p>Add more reusable functions for a certain number of DUTs.</p></li>
<li><p>Add custom setup and teardown functions</p></li>
