<section id=3D"mark-flaky-tests">
<h3>Mark Flaky Tests<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.espressif.=
com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/contribute/esp-idf-tests-with-pytest.h=
tml#mark-flaky-tests" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81</a></h3=
>
<p>Certain test cases are based on Ethernet or Wi-Fi. However, the test may=
 be flaky due to networking issues. Thus, it is possible to mark a particul=
ar test case as flaky.</p>
<p>This code example is taken from <a class=3D"reference external" href=3D"=
https://github.com/espressif/esp-idf/blob/v6.0.2/components/esp_eth/test_ap=
ps/pytest_esp_eth.py">pytest_esp_eth.py </a>.</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre i=
d=3D"codecell27"><span></span><span class=3D"nd">@pytest</span><span class=
=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">mark</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span=
 class=3D"n">flaky</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"n">reruns=
</span><span class=3D"o">=3D</span><span class=3D"mi">3</span><span class=
=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"n">reruns_delay</span><span class=3D"o">=3D<=
/span><span class=3D"mi">5</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"k">def</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"nf">te=
st_esp_eth_ip101</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"n">dut</spa=
n><span class=3D"p">:</span> <span class=3D"n">IdfDut</span><span class=3D"=
p">)</span> <span class=3D"o">-&gt;</span> <span class=3D"kc">None</span><s=
pan class=3D"p">:</span>
    <span class=3D"o">...</span>
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell27">
