<section id=3D"add-new-markers">
<h3>Add New Markers<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.espressif.c=
om/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/contribute/esp-idf-tests-with-pytest.ht=
ml#add-new-markers" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81</a></h3>
<p>We currently use two types of custom markers. The target marker indicate=
s which target chips the test case supports, and the env marker specifies t=
hat the test case should be assigned to a CI runner with the corresponding =
tag.</p>
<p>You can add new markers by adding one line under the <a class=3D"referen=
ce external" href=3D"https://github.com/espressif/esp-idf/blob/v6.0.2/pytes=
t.ini">pytest.ini</a>. If it is a marker that specifies a type of test envi=
ronment, it should be added into <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslat=
e"><span class=3D"pre">env_markers</span></code> section. Otherwise, it sho=
uld be added into <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">markers</span></code> section. The syntax should be: <code class=
=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">&lt;marker_name&gt;:<=
/span> <span class=3D"pre">&lt;marker_description&gt;</span></code>.</p>
</section>
<section id=3D"skip-auto-flash-binary">
<h3>Skip Auto Flash Binary<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.espr=
essif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/contribute/esp-idf-tests-with-py=
test.html#skip-auto-flash-binary" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=
=83=81</a></h3>
<p>Skipping auto-flash binary every time would be useful when you are debug=
ging your test script.</p>
<p>You can call pytest with <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><s=
pan class=3D"pre">--skip-autoflash</span> <span class=3D"pre">y</span></cod=
e> to achieve it.</p>
</section>
<section id=3D"record-statistics">
<h3>Record Statistics<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.espressif=
.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/contribute/esp-idf-tests-with-pytest.=
html#record-statistics" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81</a></=
h3>
<p>Sometimes you may need to record some statistics while running the tests=
, like the performance test statistics.</p>
<p>You can use <a class=3D"reference external" href=3D"https://docs.pytest.=
org/en/latest/how-to/output.html?highlight=3Djunit#record-xml-attribute">re=
cord_xml_attribute</a> fixture in your test script, and the statistics woul=
d be recorded as attributes in the JUnit report.</p>
</section>
<section id=3D"logging-system">
<h3>Logging System<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.espressif.co=
