<section id=3D"check-performance">
<h4><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">check_=
performance</span></code><a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.espre=
ssif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/contribute/esp-idf-tests-with-pyt=
est.html#check-performance" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81</=
a></h4>
<p>We provide C macros <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span c=
lass=3D"pre">TEST_PERFORMANCE_LESS_THAN</span></code> and <code class=3D"do=
cutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">TEST_PERFORMANCE_GREATER_TH=
AN</span></code> to log the performance item and check if the value is in t=
he valid range. Sometimes the performance item value could not be measured =
in C code, so we also provide a Python function for the same purpose. Pleas=
e note that using C macros is the preferred approach, since the Python func=
tion could not recognize the threshold values of the same performance item =
under different <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D=
"pre">#ifdef</span></code> blocks well.</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre i=
d=3D"codecell33"><span></span><span class=3D"k">def</span><span class=3D"w"=
> </span><span class=3D"nf">test_hello_world</span><span class=3D"p">(</spa=
n>
    <span class=3D"n">dut</span><span class=3D"p">:</span> <span class=3D"n=
">IdfDut</span><span class=3D"p">,</span>
    <span class=3D"n">check_performance</span><span class=3D"p">:</span> <s=
pan class=3D"n">Callable</span><span class=3D"p">[[</span><span class=3D"nb=
">str</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"nb">float</span><span=
 class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"nb">str</span><span class=3D"p">],</sp=
an> <span class=3D"kc">None</span><span class=3D"p">],</span>
<span class=3D"p">)</span> <span class=3D"o">-&gt;</span> <span class=3D"kc=
">None</span><span class=3D"p">:</span>
    <span class=3D"n">check_performance</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><sp=
an class=3D"s1">'RSA_2048KEY_PUBLIC_OP'</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <s=
pan class=3D"mi">123</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"s1">'e=
sp32'</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
    <span class=3D"n">check_performance</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><sp=
an class=3D"s1">'RSA_2048KEY_PUBLIC_OP'</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <s=
pan class=3D"mi">19001</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"s1">=
'esp32'</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell33">
      <svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class=3D"icon icon-tabler i=
con-tabler-copy" width=3D"44" height=3D"44" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" stroke-wi=
dth=3D"1.5" stroke=3D"#000000" fill=3D"none" stroke-linecap=3D"round" strok=
e-linejoin=3D"round">
  <title>Copy to clipboard</title>
  <path stroke=3D"none" d=3D"M0 0h24v24H0z" fill=3D"none"></path>
  <rect x=3D"8" y=3D"8" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" rx=3D"2"></rect>
  <path d=3D"M16 8v-2a2 2 0 0 0 -2 -2h-8a2 2 0 0 0 -2 2v8a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h2">=
</path>
</svg>
    </button></div>
</div>
<p>The above example would first get the threshold values of the performanc=
e item <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">RSA=
_2048KEY_PUBLIC_OP</span></code> from <a class=3D"reference external" href=
=3D"https://github.com/espressif/esp-idf/blob/v6.0.2/components/idf_test/in=
clude/idf_performance.h">components/idf_test/include/idf_performance.h</a> =
and the target-specific one <a class=3D"reference external" href=3D"https:/=
/github.com/espressif/esp-idf/blob/v6.0.2/components/idf_test/include/esp32=
/idf_performance_target.h">components/idf_test/include/esp32/idf_performanc=
e_target.h</a>, then check if the value reached the minimum limit or exceed=
ed the maximum limit.</p>
<p>Let us assume the value of <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">IDF_PERFORMANCE_MAX_RSA_2048KEY_PUBLIC_OP</span></code>=
 is 19000. so the first <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span =
class=3D"pre">check_performance</span></code> line would pass and the secon=
d one would fail with warning: <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"=
><span class=3D"pre">[Performance]</span> <span class=3D"pre">RSA_2048KEY_P=
UBLIC_OP</span> <span class=3D"pre">value</span> <span class=3D"pre">is</sp=
an> <span class=3D"pre">19001,</span> <span class=3D"pre">doesn\'t</span> <=
span class=3D"pre">meet</span> <span class=3D"pre">pass</span> <span class=
=3D"pre">standard</span> <span class=3D"pre">19000.0</span></code>.</p>
</section>
